# Agent Workflow Rules

## Blueprint selection
When a user requests a task, identify the type and use the matching blueprint:

| Request type | Blueprint | Start with |
|-------------|-----------|-----------|
| "add/implement/build" | feature-v1 | `just bp feature <ID>` |
| "fix/bug/broken" | bugfix-v1 | `just bp bugfix <ID>` |
| "refactor/clean/extract" | refactor-v1 | `just bp refactor <ID>` |
| "review/check PR" | review-v1 | `just bp review <ID>` |
| "release/deploy" | release-v1 | `just bp release <version>` |

## Run initialization
Before starting any blueprint execution:
```
./scripts/plan-init.sh <TASK-ID> <blueprint>
```
This creates `.ai/runs/<TASK-ID>/` with the right structure.

## Priority assessment
Before starting work, assign priority:

- **P0**: Any mention of security, migration, data loss, unclear root cause → escalate to Claude
- **P1**: Features, refactors with known scope → Claude plans, Codex executes
- **P2**: Boilerplate, docs, simple tests → Codex local
- **P3**: Triage, search, changelogs → Codex local cheap

## Worktree rules
- Never work directly on main branch for blueprint runs
- Create worktree: `./scripts/worktree.sh create <TASK-ID>`
- Clean up after merge: `./scripts/worktree.sh clean <TASK-ID>`

## Verification gate
`scripts/ai-check.sh` must pass before:
- Marking any stage complete
- Proposing PR
- Merging worktree back
